{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-05-01T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Can you picture more than 10,800 square kilometres of protected wilderness? That's Jasper National Park in Alberta, Canada. Established in 1907 as part of a growing network of protected landscapes in the Canadian Rockies, it was designated a national park in 1930. The park reflects both conservation efforts and much older Indigenous connections, including those of the Nakoda and Secwépemc peoples. Its terrain ranges from glacier-fed rivers and alpine meadows to dense conifer forests dominated by spruce and pine.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.GreenJasper_EN-IN3195299837_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.GreenJasper_EN-IN3195299837_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The magic of Jasper","Title":"Small lake and marsh in Jasper National Park in Alberta, Canada","Copyright":"© Don White/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/52.873398,-117.954308/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=52.873398,-117.954308;S9;Jasper National Park, Alberta, Canada&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260502_GreenJasper\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Jasper+National+Park+Alberta&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260501_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260502_GreenJasper"},"Ssd":"20260502","Name":"GreenJasper","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"3195299837","FullDateString":"2 May, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"If states threw birthday parties, Maharashtra would book the largest venue. Every 1 May, it marks its formation in 1960, when the bilingual Bombay State was split to create a Marathi-speaking region. The message was clear: language matters, but so does having a voice.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MaharashtraDay2026_EN-IN0347211798_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MaharashtraDay2026_EN-IN0347211798_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"A day carved in pride","Title":"Kailasa Temple, Ellora Caves, Maharashtra","Copyright":"© mazzzur/iStock/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/20.02117,75.179573/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=20.02117,75.179573;S9;Ellora Caves, Maharashtra&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260501_MaharashtraDay2026\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Maharashtra+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260430_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260501_MaharashtraDay2026"},"Ssd":"20260501","Name":"MaharashtraDay2026","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"0347211798","FullDateString":"1 May, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Imagine a flower sparking a financial frenzy. Sounds unlikely, right? Yet in the 1630s, tulips did exactly that in the Netherlands. During tulip mania, rare bulbs became luxury items traded for astonishing sums—some valued at prices comparable to a house. Why so valuable? Unusual colours and striped patterns were scarce and unpredictable, and collectors wanted the rarest varieties they could find.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.DutchTulips_EN-IN3094932538_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.DutchTulips_EN-IN3094932538_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Tulips run the show","Title":"Grape hyacinths and tulips, Keukenhof Gardens, Lisse, Netherlands","Copyright":"© Martin Ruegner/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/52.26889,4.547222/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=52.26889,4.547222;S9;Keukenhof Gardens, Lisse, Netherlands&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260430_DutchTulips\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Keukenhof+Gardens&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260429_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260430_DutchTulips"},"Ssd":"20260430","Name":"DutchTulips","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"3094932538","FullDateString":"30 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Ships leaving Lisbon once passed a small stone tower before meeting the wide Atlantic. That tower, standing on the bank of the Tagus River, served as both a guardian and a farewell. Say hello to Belém Tower—a fortress that watched Portugal sail into the Age of Exploration.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BelemTowerBank_EN-IN2907801378_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BelemTowerBank_EN-IN2907801378_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"History anchored in stone","Title":"Belém Tower on the bank of the Tagus River, Lisbon, Portugal","Copyright":"© f9photos/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/38.69165,-9.215943/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=38.69165,-9.215943;S9;Belém Tower, Lisbon, Portugal&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260429_BelemTowerBank\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Belem+Tower&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260428_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260429_BelemTowerBank"},"Ssd":"20260429","Name":"BelemTowerBank","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"2907801378","FullDateString":"29 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"The spectacled bear, also known as the Andean bear, is the only South American bear of the Ursidae family. Inhabiting the northern and central Andes Mountains, it dwells primarily in forested areas and feeds mainly on shoots and fruit. Pale markings around the eyes often resemble eyeglasses, or 'spectacles,' giving the species its distinctive name.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AndeanBear_EN-IN2726227738_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AndeanBear_EN-IN2726227738_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Spectacles in the wild","Title":"Spectacled bear resting in tree, Ecuador","Copyright":"© Andy Rouse/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Each spectacled bear has unique facial markings, which scientists use to identify and track individuals in the wild.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260428_AndeanBear\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Spectacled+bear&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260427_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260428_AndeanBear"},"Ssd":"20260428","Name":"AndeanBear","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"2726227738","FullDateString":"28 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Designed by architect Giuseppe Mengoni and completed in 1877, the Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II in Milan, Italy, is one of the world's oldest and most famous shopping arcades. Located between Piazza del Duomo and Piazza della Scala, it features a stunning glass-and-iron roof and an elegant, octagonal layout. Affectionately known as 'Milan's living room,' the Galleria is home to high-end boutiques, historic cafés such as Caffè Biffi and Camparino in Galleria and renowned restaurants.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MilanGalleria_EN-IN2538393019_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MilanGalleria_EN-IN2538393019_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Glass with class","Title":"The glass dome of Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II, Milan, Italy","Copyright":"© PhillipMinnis/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/45.466179,9.18992/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=45.466179,9.18992;S9;Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II, Milan, Italy&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260427_MilanGalleria\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Galleria+Vittorio+Emanuele+II+Milan+Italy&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260426_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260427_MilanGalleria"},"Ssd":"20260427","Name":"MilanGalleria","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"2538393019","FullDateString":"27 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Spring brings apple trees to life with clouds of soft pink blossoms. Their delicate petals brighten orchards and hillsides, standing out against clear blue skies as the season shifts from winter towards warmer days. These blooms attract pollinators such as bees and butterflies, helping fruit trees produce the apples that will grow later in the year.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AppleBlossoms_EN-IN2309236905_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AppleBlossoms_EN-IN2309236905_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Bloom boom","Title":"Pink apple blossoms, Avila Beach, California, United States","Copyright":"© Mimi Ditchie Photography/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/35.177404,-120.733528/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=35.177404,-120.733528;S9;Avila Beach, California, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260426_AppleBlossoms\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Apple+tree&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260425_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260426_AppleBlossoms"},"Ssd":"20260426","Name":"AppleBlossoms","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"2309236905","FullDateString":"26 Apr, 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Water is the architect of Krka National Park in Croatia, shaping emerald pools and layered waterfalls along the Krka River. Today's image highlights Skradinski Buk, the park's most famous waterfall system, where multiple streams spill over travertine terraces in a dense forest near the village of Lozovac.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SkradinskiBuk_EN-IN5310888144_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SkradinskiBuk_EN-IN5310888144_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The architect of Krka","Title":"Skradinski Buk Waterfall in Krka National Park, Croatia","Copyright":"© Amazing Aerial Agency/Adobe Stock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/43.805592,15.963964/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=43.805592,15.963964;S9;Skradinski Buk Waterfall, Krka National Park, Lozovac, Croatia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260509_SkradinskiBuk\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Krka+National+Park+Croatia&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260508_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260509_SkradinskiBuk"},"Ssd":"20260509","Name":"SkradinskiBuk","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"5310888144","FullDateString":"9 May, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"World Donkey Day celebrates one of humanity's most quietly capable partners. Donkeys have worked alongside people for thousands of years, prized for their endurance, sharp memory and sure-footed confidence on rugged ground. Often mistaken for stubborn, they are actually careful thinkers—pausing to assess risk rather than rushing into trouble.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SardinianDonkey_EN-IN5118136670_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SardinianDonkey_EN-IN5118136670_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"More than a hee-haw","Title":"Sardinian donkey mare and foal, France","Copyright":"© Klein & Hubert/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"A mule is the offspring of a male donkey and a female horse.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260508_SardinianDonkey\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Donkey+animal&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260507_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260508_SardinianDonkey"},"Ssd":"20260508","Name":"SardinianDonkey","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"5118136670","FullDateString":"8 May, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Stretching across the Sonoran Desert in southwestern Arizona, United States, Kofa National Wildlife Refuge is a land of sharp peaks, wide skies and surprising life. The refuge was established in 1939 to protect desert bighorn sheep, whose sure-footed silhouettes still define the rugged landscape.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.Kofa_EN-IN4942655895_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.Kofa_EN-IN4942655895_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Desert, drawn wide","Title":"Kofa National Wildlife Refuge, Arizona, United States","Copyright":"© Denis Tangney Jr/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/33.237633,-114.011215/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=33.237633,-114.011215;S9;Kofa National Wildlife Refuge, Arizona, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260507_Kofa\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Kofa+National+Wildlife+Refuge&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260506_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260507_Kofa"},"Ssd":"20260507","Name":"Kofa","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"4942655895","FullDateString":"7 May, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Located on the eastern Balkan Peninsula, Bulgaria sits at the crossroads of Europe and Asia, where ancient cultures, fertile landscapes and shifting climates converge.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BulgariaPlains_EN-IN4718054909_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BulgariaPlains_EN-IN4718054909_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Plains under pressure","Title":"Thunderstorm above the plains, Bulgaria","Copyright":"© Revolu7ion93/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/42.75,25.5/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=42.75,25.5;S9;Bulgaria&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260506_BulgariaPlains\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Bulgaria&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260505_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260506_BulgariaPlains"},"Ssd":"20260506","Name":"BulgariaPlains","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"4718054909","FullDateString":"6 May, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"At the far edge of Ynys Llanddwyn, where the land quietly gives way to sea, Tŵr Mawr Lighthouse stands watch without making a fuss. It is not tall, not flashy, but it knows its purpose—and it keeps it bright.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TwrMawrLighthouse2026_EN-IN1989617864_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TwrMawrLighthouse2026_EN-IN1989617864_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Light at the end of the isle","Title":"Tŵr Mawr Lighthouse, Ynys Llanddwyn, Anglesey, Wales","Copyright":"© Lukas Bischoff/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/53.13707,-4.412761/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=53.13707,-4.412761;S9;Ynys Llanddwyn, Isle of Anglesey, Wales&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260505_TwrMawrLighthouse2026\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Twr+Mawr+Lighthouse&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260504_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260505_TwrMawrLighthouse2026"},"Ssd":"20260505","Name":"TwrMawrLighthouse2026","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"1989617864","FullDateString":"5 May, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"May the 4th be with you! On Star Wars Day, reality cosplays as science fiction and dares you to tell the difference. Our image takes us to Ksar Ouled Soltane in Tunisia's Tataouine district, where stacked clay granaries rise like sand‑coloured fortresses. Dating back to the 15th century, this storehouse complex was built by Berber communities to protect harvests from heat, theft and time. Function first. Beauty as a side effect.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.KsarOuledSoltane_EN-IN1772152584_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.KsarOuledSoltane_EN-IN1772152584_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Sci‑fi, Earth‑made","Title":"Ksar Ouled Soltane, Tataouine district in southern Tunisia","Copyright":"© Dark_Eni/Getty Images Plus","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/32.793106,10.518624/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=32.793106,10.518624;S9;Ksar Ouled Soltane, Tataouine, Tunisia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260504_KsarOuledSoltane\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Star+Wars+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260503_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260504_KsarOuledSoltane"},"Ssd":"20260504","Name":"KsarOuledSoltane","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"1772152584","FullDateString":"4 May, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"High above the savanna in Kenya's Masai Mara, a leopard curls up on a tree branch, napping as the grasslands glow at sunset. On International Leopard Day, observed on 3 May, we celebrate one of the world's most adaptable big cats. Leopards roam across Africa and parts of Asia, thriving in habitats that range from forests and mountains to open savannas. Their spotted coats are unique to each individual, like fingerprints, and their powerful climbing skills allow them to stash prey high in trees, out of reach of scavengers.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MasaiLeopard_EN-IN3617072692_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MasaiLeopard_EN-IN3617072692_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Savanna afterglow","Title":"Leopard sleeping in a tree in the savannah, Masai Mara National Reserve, Kenya","Copyright":"© Klein & Hubert/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Leopards have lost about 75% of their historical distribution and are classified as 'vulnerable' by the IUCN.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260503_MasaiLeopard\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=International+Leopard+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260502_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260503_MasaiLeopard"},"Ssd":"20260503","Name":"MasaiLeopard","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"3617072692","FullDateString":"3 May, 2026"}],"LocStrings":{"LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD":"दिन की छवि","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD_LEARN_MORE":"अधिक जानें","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_DONATE_NOW":"अभी दान दें","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_FACT":"त्वरित तथ्य:","LOC_HOMEPAGE_GALLERY_CARD_TITLE":"हाल ही की मुख पृष्ठ छवियाँ","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_GALLERY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"{0} की मुख्य पृष्ठ छवि","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_TITLE":"इतिहास में आज के दिन","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"{0}, {1} में इस दिन","LOC_HOMEPAGE_SHARE_TOOLTIP":"आज का Bing मुखपृष्ठ साझा करें","LOC_HOMEPAGE_WALLPAPERDOWNLOAD_TOOLTIP":"इस छवि को डाउनलोड करें. इस छवि का उपयोग केवल वॉलपेपर तक प्रतिबंधित है.","LOC_MUSCARD_DOWNLO